Here, take a look.

797
00:45:53,918 --> 00:45:55,261
Have you seen?

798
00:45:57,171 --> 00:45:59,014
Yeah, you know her.
Where did she go?

799
00:46:00,841 --> 00:46:02,514
But she's gone.
Oh!

800
00:46:02,843 --> 00:46:04,436
Well, yeah...

801
00:46:05,471 --> 00:46:06,814
But where?

802
00:46:16,190 --> 00:46:17,191
(SIGHS)

803
00:46:38,713 --> 00:46:40,135
Hey,
Meg.

804
00:46:46,429 --> 00:46:47,601
Riley?

805
00:46:48,389 --> 00:46:49,436
Hey.

806
00:46:52,727 --> 00:46:53,728
Hi.

807
00:46:55,271 --> 00:46:57,069
You're not
following me, are you?

808
00:46:57,606 --> 00:46:58,698
Following?

809
00:46:58,941 --> 00:47:00,693
No. No, I didn’t...

810
00:47:06,741 --> 00:47:07,993
You okay?

811
00:47:12,913 --> 00:47:14,711
Rm good. (CHUCKLES)

812
00:47:17,084 --> 00:47:18,427
So, where's your bus?

813
00:47:22,590 --> 00:47:25,594
It left us behind
a long time ago.

814
00:47:27,928 --> 00:47:29,430
Stupid bus.

815
00:47:32,892 --> 00:47:34,235
Cordelia!

816
00:47:34,727 --> 00:47:36,104
Oh, hey. What's up?

817
00:47:37,646 --> 00:47:39,068
You're late.

818
00:47:39,482 --> 00:47:40,904
Late for what?

819
00:47:43,778 --> 00:47:45,200
Are you...
What?

820
00:47:45,279 --> 00:47:47,782
You sound...
Something different.

821
00:47:49,784 --> 00:47:51,707
Chip-chop, spit-spot,
come on, let's go!

822
00:47:51,786 --> 00:47:53,959
Off we go! Quickly, come on!

823
00:47:55,998 --> 00:47:57,124
Let's go.

824
00:47:57,208 --> 00:47:58,209
Okay.

825
00:48:41,794 --> 00:48:43,262
Did somebody get flowers?

826
00:48:45,673 --> 00:48:46,720
Meg?

827
00:48:48,175 --> 00:48:49,347
Grace?

828
00:48:55,015 --> 00:48:56,016
Me.

829
00:48:59,145 --> 00:49:01,443
(EXHALES) "Emma, please
allow me the honor..."

830
00:49:01,814 --> 00:49:03,987
Da-da-da-da-da-da-da. .

831
00:49:04,066 --> 00:49:06,364
"I'll pick you up at 8:00.
Domenico"

832
00:49:08,863 --> 00:49:10,206
(SNIFFING)

833
00:49:16,162 --> 00:49:17,835
Cheers, thank you.

834
00:49:19,665 --> 00:49:20,882
Okay, all right.
Yeah?

835
00:49:21,208 --> 00:49:23,051
All right, this is what
you've been waiting for.

836
00:49:23,127 --> 00:49:25,004
Bring it on.
I want to see this.

837
00:49:25,796 --> 00:49:26,797
I mean to just...

838
00:49:26,881 --> 00:49:27,882
(LAUGHS)

839
00:49:30,342 --> 00:49:31,969
Au right, I'll have a go.
All right.

840
00:49:32,094 --> 00:49:33,721
You want to? Go?

841
00:49:34,054 --> 00:49:35,101
Ready?

842
00:49:35,181 --> 00:49:36,433
Go ahead.

843
00:49:39,560 --> 00:49:41,483
There we go. That's it.
You actually know how to do it.

844
00:49:41,562 --> 00:49:42,984
That's good.

845
00:50:04,919 --> 00:50:07,513
Bonjour Lucille,
this is Mademoiselle Scott.

846
00:50:07,588 --> 00:50:09,590
Lucille will take care of you,
she'll show you to your room.

847
00:50:10,049 --> 00:50:11,175
Where are you going?

848
00:50:11,884 --> 00:50:13,101
I have to go change.

849
00:50:13,594 --> 00:50:15,096
Change?
I'll see you on the field.

850
00:50:15,679 --> 00:50:17,226
Cordelia!

851
00:50:19,975 --> 00:50:21,192
There you are.

852
00:50:21,268 --> 00:50:22,360
Ah, Aunt Alicia.

853
00:50:22,436 --> 00:50:24,359
I’d love to stay and chat,

854
00:50:24,438 --> 00:50:27,988
but I must change, so...

855
00:50:33,113 --> 00:50:34,330
Really!

856
00:50:36,742 --> 00:50:37,914
Merci.

857
00:50:56,095 --> 00:50:58,097
Polo, how hard can it be?

858
00:51:15,990 --> 00:51:18,334
Hey! I think we are
going the other way.

859
00:51:18,534 --> 00:51:21,788
Oh, right. See, at home they usually just bring the ball to me.

860
00:51:21,870 --> 00:51:23,964
Right. The other way. Okay.

861
00:51:24,039 --> 00:51:25,291
Go right.
(CLICKS TONGUE)

862
00:51:26,834 --> 00:51:29,838
Your niece plays
with spirit.

863
00:51:30,713 --> 00:51:33,387
Usually with more
finesse than spirit.

864
00:51:41,515 --> 00:51:42,687
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

865
00:51:47,646 --> 00:51:49,148
(I WANT THE SKY PLAYING)

866
00:51:49,231 --> 00:51:51,859
I'm ready, ready to run free

867
00:51:51,942 --> 00:51:53,660
That's a nice one.

868
00:51:53,902 --> 00:51:54,994
Thank you.

869
00:51:55,070 --> 00:51:58,244
I 'd like to know
what lies beyond the blue sea

870
00:51:58,324 --> 00:52:01,498
You live once,
so drink the honey

871
00:52:01,577 --> 00:52:02,829
(WHOOPS)

872
00:52:02,911 --> 00:52:07,041
I learn my lessons
from the birds and the bees

873
00:52:09,627 --> 00:52:13,973
I want the sky to open wide

874
00:52:14,048 --> 00:52:18,303
Illuminate this fire inside

875
00:52:18,385 --> 00:52:19,932
I want the sky

876
00:52:21,805 --> 00:52:24,399
So, you just go
wherever you like?

877
00:52:25,225 --> 00:52:26,522
Yeah, that's the idea.

878
00:52:27,394 --> 00:52:28,646
For how long?

879
00:52:28,729 --> 00:52:30,823
I'll let you know
when I'm done.

880
00:52:31,231 --> 00:52:32,858
And your parents
are okay with this?

881
00:52:34,610 --> 00:52:36,988
I think they were just happy to see
me walk out of there, you know?

882
00:52:38,364 --> 00:52:40,583
What, did they say you'd never
walk again or something?

883
00:52:45,788 --> 00:52:48,086
I was never much good at being
told what I couldn't do.

884
00:52:49,708 --> 00:52:53,758
But I was in hospital for a
year just flat on my back.

885
00:52:58,384 --> 00:52:59,886
I hate hospitals.

886
00:53:03,889 --> 00:53:07,484
My teammates would come and
visit in the beginning,

887
00:53:09,103 --> 00:53:10,275
but after a while,

888
00:53:11,730 --> 00:53:13,698
I was just a reminder
of what could happen to them.

889
00:53:15,609 --> 00:53:16,952
Bad fall,

890
00:53:17,027 --> 00:53:20,952
get hit in the wrong place,
never play rugby again.

891
00:53:24,451 --> 00:53:25,953
Anyway,

892
00:53:26,036 --> 00:53:27,879
trekking around for a while

893
00:53:27,955 --> 00:53:29,207
just seemed like
the best way back.

894
00:53:43,262 --> 00:53:44,639
You miss your mum.

895
00:53:56,275 --> 00:53:58,027
I can't find my way back.

896
00:54:01,238 --> 00:54:04,959
I went to the hospital to see
her every day she was there.

897
00:54:07,161 --> 00:54:08,583
Almost two years.

898
00:54:09,955 --> 00:54:11,332
That's a long time.

899
00:54:14,334 --> 00:54:15,506
Not long enough.

900
00:54:20,924 --> 00:54:22,141
(SIGHS)

901
00:54:23,010 --> 00:54:27,561
Everyone was so nice, and
understanding, and comforting, and...

902
00:54:29,141 --> 00:54:31,109
I just wanted to scream.

903
00:54:35,689 --> 00:54:36,690
Do it.

904
00:54:39,568 --> 00:54:41,866
Go on. Scream.

905
00:54:42,362 --> 00:54:43,454
Just do it.

906
00:54:44,031 --> 00:54:46,033
Look, I won't even listen.
I won't listen.

907
00:54:57,419 --> 00:54:58,671
I can't.

908
00:55:09,223 --> 00:55:10,224
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

909
00:55:28,951 --> 00:55:30,203
(LAUGHS)

910
00:55:37,167 --> 00:55:38,168
(RINGING)

911
00:55:38,377 --> 00:55:40,254
Is it all right if I take her?
I'd love to brush her down.

912
00:55:40,712 --> 00:55:42,134
What?
The ball. Take it!

913
00:55:42,506 --> 00:55:44,133
This is Cordelia.

914
00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:47,477
Hello?

915
00:55:50,472 --> 00:55:51,689
Hello?

916
00:55:52,933 --> 00:55:54,856
(SPECTATORS APPLAUDING)

917
00:55:56,436 --> 00:55:57,813
Who is this?

918
00:56:02,276 --> 00:56:04,370
Is it all right if I take her?
I'd love to brush her down.

919
00:56:04,444 --> 00:56:06,367
Really?
Yeah, I've got her.

920
00:56:07,990 --> 00:56:09,082
Odd.

921
00:56:09,283 --> 00:56:11,126
You've never been one
to clear up after yourself.

922
00:56:12,619 --> 00:56:14,621
A new leaf, a new me.

923
00:56:15,289 --> 00:56:16,791
It appears
you've made a friend.

924
00:56:17,583 --> 00:56:19,677
I know.
isn't she a beauty?

925
00:56:20,711 --> 00:56:22,759
Remember that darling
pony you had as a girl?

926
00:56:23,297 --> 00:56:24,970
What was its name again?

927
00:56:28,260 --> 00:56:30,479
My childhood, please!
You know I never look back.

928
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:32,181
Oh, you remember
the black one

929
00:56:32,264 --> 00:56:34,062
with the little white
star on his forehead.

930
00:56:35,809 --> 00:56:37,152
Yes. Uh...

931
00:56:37,227 --> 00:56:39,525
The one with the star.

932
00:56:39,605 --> 00:56:41,482
I called him Blaze.

933
00:56:42,274 --> 00:56:43,446
Blaze?

934
00:56:44,818 --> 00:56:46,912
I really should get her
back to the stables, so...

935
00:56:48,155 --> 00:56:50,157
The resemblance
is astonishing.

936
00:56:51,241 --> 00:56:52,993
But Cordelia rides
English saddle.

937
00:56:53,952 --> 00:56:56,501
And you, if I'm not mistaken,
were taught to ride Western.

938
00:56:57,372 --> 00:56:58,840
Heaven forbid.

939
00:56:58,916 --> 00:57:00,759
I'm just a little out of
practice, that's all.

940
00:57:00,918 --> 00:57:03,421
Well, this is a new low
even for Cordelia.

941
00:57:04,338 --> 00:57:07,137
To hire a look-alike
to stand in her stead

942
00:57:07,215 --> 00:57:10,094
at a charity event
organized just for her

943
00:57:10,177 --> 00:57:12,179
while she's off partying.

944
00:57:12,387 --> 00:57:13,809
I don't know
if it's the champagne

945
00:57:13,889 --> 00:57:15,141
or the sunlight
that's got to you.

946
00:57:15,223 --> 00:57:17,601
Oh, I will call
security immediately.

947
00:57:17,684 --> 00:57:20,733
No, you can't.
The charity!

948
00:57:22,105 --> 00:57:23,607
Look, I promise you

949
00:57:23,690 --> 00:57:26,409
that I will do whatever is
expected of Cordelia tomorrow.

950
00:57:27,319 --> 00:57:29,242
I'm not about to stand in the
way of helping those kids.

951
00:57:31,365 --> 00:57:32,457
Are you?

952
00:57:34,868 --> 00:57:35,960
BERNARD: Alicia.

953
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:41,462
No one must ever know.
Is that clear?

954
00:57:41,541 --> 00:57:42,713
Crystal.

955
00:57:42,876 --> 00:57:45,254
Here you are.
What a wonderful match.

956
00:57:45,545 --> 00:57:47,343
I was just
congratulating Cordelia.

957
00:57:48,632 --> 00:57:49,975
The ambassador
is ready for us.

958
00:57:50,050 --> 00:57:51,518
Oh. Shall we?

959
00:57:53,679 --> 00:57:57,274
If you muck this up, you
will have me to answer to.

960
00:57:57,724 --> 00:58:00,273
Both of you.
Pass it on.

961
00:58:14,783 --> 00:58:15,830
Oh.

962
00:58:21,039 --> 00:58:22,256
(SIGHS)

963
00:58:25,002 --> 00:58:27,096
Bling,bling,bling,bling,
bling,bling,bling.

964
00:58:39,975 --> 00:58:41,943
Who are you
hiding from?

965
00:58:42,936 --> 00:58:44,028
Hey.

966
00:58:58,827 --> 00:59:00,295
You ride very well.

967
00:59:02,414 --> 00:59:04,587
It's one of the two things
my father taught me.

968
00:59:05,125 --> 00:59:06,297
And the other?

969
00:59:10,589 --> 00:59:11,590
(WHISTLING)

970
00:59:11,673 --> 00:59:12,765
(HORSES NEIGHING)

971
00:59:12,841 --> 00:59:14,184
(LAUGHING)

972
00:59:14,634 --> 00:59:16,807
It's actually more handy
than you might think.

973
00:59:18,263 --> 00:59:19,264
(BLOWS)

974
00:59:20,891 --> 00:59:23,144
No, here. Put your
fingers like this

975
00:59:27,022 --> 00:59:29,775
and now curl your
tongue like that.

976
00:59:32,069 --> 00:59:33,412
Now you try.

977
00:59:34,905 --> 00:59:36,373
(SPUTTERING)

978
00:59:36,448 --> 00:59:37,745
(LAUGHING)

979
00:59:37,824 --> 00:59:39,451
That's terrible.

980
00:59:39,826 --> 00:59:41,373
Well, I'll work on it.

981
00:59:41,828 --> 00:59:43,171
I think you should.

982
00:59:51,421 --> 00:59:52,673
You're not what
I expected.

983
00:59:53,340 --> 00:59:54,432
No?

984
00:59:54,508 --> 00:59:55,760
You're different.

985
00:59:57,177 --> 00:59:58,269
Different?

986
00:59:59,971 --> 01:00:01,223
Different is good.

987
01:00:03,016 --> 01:00:04,188
Is it?

988
01:00:04,518 --> 01:00:06,191
You make me think it is.

989
01:00:06,812 --> 01:00:08,530
You make me
feel different.

990
01:00:10,941 --> 01:00:12,067
Sorry.

991
01:00:12,359 --> 01:00:13,406
Why?

992
01:00:13,860 --> 01:00:15,203
Mostly I always
feel the same.

993
01:00:15,904 --> 01:00:19,374
Same people, same
conversations, same parties.

994
01:00:20,867 --> 01:00:22,494
None of it means anything.

995
01:00:23,870 --> 01:00:25,463
But you help people.

996
01:00:26,123 --> 01:00:28,876
I mean, you're raising
money, building schools.

997
01:00:30,544 --> 01:00:32,467
I wish I were part of
something that important.

998
01:00:33,380 --> 01:00:35,303
But that's my father.
That's not me.

999
01:00:37,300 --> 01:00:38,802
I do nothing.

1000
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:40,887
I've never been
to those schools.

1001
01:00:40,971 --> 01:00:43,565
I've never been
to Africa, to Romania.

1002
01:00:44,683 --> 01:00:46,230
I'm only faking
my way through.

1003
01:00:46,893 --> 01:00:48,361
I know what
that feels like.

1004
01:00:50,730 --> 01:00:52,152
But there is nothing
fake about you.

1005
01:00:57,654 --> 01:00:59,873
I want to
show you something.

1006
01:01:06,746 --> 01:01:08,373
(MOUNTAIN AND THE SEA PLAYING)

1007
01:01:08,456 --> 01:01:12,586
You call me a mountain

1008
01:01:14,171 --> 01:01:17,892
And I call you the sea

1009
01:01:20,385 --> 01:01:25,983
You can move me
if you want to...

1010
01:01:26,766 --> 01:01:28,109
Thank you.

1011
01:01:44,492 --> 01:01:46,335
And then we're gonna go
meet his friends

1012
01:01:46,411 --> 01:01:47,958
and then we're
gonna go dancing!

1013
01:01:48,038 --> 01:01:50,132
Meg, what has
gotten into you?

1014
01:01:50,207 --> 01:01:51,424
I know.

1015
01:01:52,626 --> 01:01:53,627
(SIGHS)

1016
01:01:57,297 --> 01:01:58,640
I'm sorry.

1017
01:02:01,176 --> 01:02:02,428
Me, too.

1018
01:02:04,846 --> 01:02:06,598
Oh. (LAUGHS)

1019
01:02:09,684 --> 01:02:10,776
Hey, mate.

1020
01:02:23,198 --> 01:02:24,324
What?

1021
01:02:24,532 --> 01:02:25,875
The necklace.

1022
01:02:27,994 --> 01:02:29,917
There's the Meg
that I know.

1023
01:02:29,996 --> 01:02:31,373
What were you thinking?

1024
01:02:32,666 --> 01:02:33,883
Stay classy, Meg.

1025
01:02:44,386 --> 01:02:45,478
RILEY: You good?

1026
01:02:46,680 --> 01:02:48,523
Yeah. I'm perfect.

1027
01:03:08,243 --> 01:03:09,586
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1028
01:03:11,746 --> 01:03:13,293
First class.

1029
01:03:14,291 --> 01:03:16,214
(TAKE IT EASY PLAYING)

1030
01:03:16,835 --> 01:03:21,636
Relax, take it easy

1031
01:03:21,715 --> 01:03:24,810
For there is nothing
that we can do

1032
01:03:24,884 --> 01:03:29,856
Relax, take it easy

1033
01:03:29,931 --> 01:03:32,605
Blame it on me
or blame it on you

1034
01:03:32,684 --> 01:03:35,483
Relax, take it easy

1035
01:03:35,562 --> 01:03:36,905
(LAUGHING)

1036
01:03:37,355 --> 01:03:39,403
(ALL CHATTERING IN FRENCH)

1037
01:04:02,839 --> 01:04:04,136
Jerome.

1038
01:04:14,601 --> 01:04:15,773
Merci.

1039
01:04:18,104 --> 01:04:19,447
Excuse me.

1040
01:04:22,817 --> 01:04:24,160
There are people for that.

1041
01:04:26,237 --> 01:04:28,331
Yeah, I know.

1042
01:04:46,174 --> 01:04:47,847
Give me your hand.

1043
01:04:48,885 --> 01:04:50,228
Thank you.

1044
01:04:54,516 --> 01:04:55,608
Wow.

1045
01:05:10,156 --> 01:05:11,624
THEO: I'm trying
to impress you.

1046
01:05:11,699 --> 01:05:13,827
GRACE: Mmm.
So far, so good.

1047
01:05:29,050 --> 01:05:33,681
When I was little, I had a snow
globe of the Eiffel Tower,

1048
01:05:34,931 --> 01:05:37,354
and when you
wound it up it played

1049
01:05:37,434 --> 01:05:38,981
La Vie En Rose.

1050
01:05:40,437 --> 01:05:42,030
(LA VIE EN ROSE PLAYING)

1051
01:05:43,148 --> 01:05:45,697
And when I shook it,
the snow inside sparkled.

1052
01:05:49,028 --> 01:05:50,325
(HUMMING)

1053
01:05:53,658 --> 01:05:57,708
When you kiss me
heaven sighs

1054
01:05:57,787 --> 01:05:59,334
It was magical.

1055
01:06:00,957 --> 01:06:02,049
Just like this.

1056
01:06:02,125 --> 01:06:06,301
I see la vie en rose

1057
01:06:06,379 --> 01:06:07,471
Just wait.

1058
01:06:07,547 --> 01:06:11,552
When you press me
to your heart

1059
01:06:12,177 --> 01:06:15,431
I'm in a world apart

1060
01:06:15,513 --> 01:06:19,438
A world where roses bloom

1061
01:06:20,852 --> 01:06:22,399
And when you speak

1062
