(INQUIRING IN FRENCH)

1332
01:27:23,947 --> 01:27:25,039
(DOORBELL CHIMING)

1333
01:27:29,327 --> 01:27:30,670
Finally...

1334
01:27:33,498 --> 01:27:35,045
We can explain.

1335
01:27:35,792 --> 01:27:37,510
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1336
01:27:39,504 --> 01:27:41,506
(RESISTING IN FRENCH)

1337
01:27:45,510 --> 01:27:47,057
GRACE: Listen...
Save your sorries for the police.

1338
01:27:47,137 --> 01:27:48,605
Wait, wait.
The police?

1339
01:27:48,680 --> 01:27:49,852
Oh, please!

1340
01:27:49,931 --> 01:27:51,649
But it's right here.
I have it.

1341
01:27:51,725 --> 01:27:53,022
Exactly! You have it!

1342
01:27:53,101 --> 01:27:55,069
MEG: Look, this wasn’t planned.

1343
01:27:55,145 --> 01:27:57,193
It's just a case of
mistaken identity.

1344
01:28:00,484 --> 01:28:02,282
It's impersonation
and it's a crime,

1345
01:28:02,360 --> 01:28:04,033
one I'm putting
a stop to this instant.

1346
01:28:04,362 --> 01:28:05,488
But the auction...
Oh!

1347
01:28:06,531 --> 01:28:09,284
Let me assure you that there
will be no auction now.

1348
01:28:09,493 --> 01:28:11,791
Hey! People are
counting on her!

1349
01:28:11,870 --> 01:28:13,872
(STAMMERING)
Or on you... What?

1350
01:28:14,623 --> 01:28:16,125
That's not my problem.

1351
01:28:18,502 --> 01:28:20,049
Don't touch the phone.

1352
01:28:20,837 --> 01:28:22,054
Or what?

1353
01:28:25,425 --> 01:28:27,598
I promise you it
is a false alarm.

1354
01:28:27,677 --> 01:28:28,644
She said everything was fine.
Quoi?

1355
01:28:28,720 --> 01:28:29,812
(IN FRENCH)

1356
01:28:29,888 --> 01:28:32,061
But why am I speaking English?

1357
01:28:32,182 --> 01:28:33,479
CORDELIA: No!

1358
01:28:35,435 --> 01:28:37,312
Ow! You let me up.

1359
01:28:37,562 --> 01:28:39,235
Now what do we do?

1360
01:28:39,648 --> 01:28:41,525
Cordelia?
RECEPTIONIST: Mademoiselle?

1361
01:28:41,733 --> 01:28:42,905
Help! Mmm!

1362
01:28:44,486 --> 01:28:45,908
(SQUEALING)

1363
01:28:46,530 --> 01:28:48,749
Mademoiselle,
open the door!

1364
01:28:48,824 --> 01:28:50,747
GRACE: Just a minute.

1365
01:28:50,826 --> 01:28:51,918
Give me the...

1366
01:28:54,788 --> 01:28:56,005
(SPEAKING FRENCH)

1367
01:28:58,375 --> 01:28:59,467
Bonjour.

1368
01:28:59,668 --> 01:29:00,669
Hello.
Hi.

1369
01:29:01,086 --> 01:29:02,178
Mademoiselle.

1370
01:29:03,088 --> 01:29:05,887
Excusez-moi. We had a call.
There was a robbery?

1371
01:29:05,966 --> 01:29:08,060
Oh, no.
A misunderstanding.

1372
01:29:08,134 --> 01:29:09,351
YOU see?

1373
01:29:09,427 --> 01:29:10,804
Yes, she couldn't
find her necklace.

1374
01:29:10,887 --> 01:29:11,934
What? Where is she?

1375
01:29:12,013 --> 01:29:13,014
I'm right here.

1376
01:29:13,098 --> 01:29:14,145
RECEPTIONIST:
There she is.

1377
01:29:14,224 --> 01:29:15,396
Bonjour
mademoiselle.

1378
01:29:15,475 --> 01:29:16,727
Bonjour.

1379
01:29:19,312 --> 01:29:21,690
Theo, could you help me?

1380
01:29:22,774 --> 01:29:24,242
I can't quite
manage the clasp.

1381
01:29:25,819 --> 01:29:27,241
But tell me,
we heard a scream.

1382
01:29:28,947 --> 01:29:29,994
Oh!

1383
01:29:31,116 --> 01:29:33,494
When she found
the necklace,

1384
01:29:35,579 --> 01:29:39,584
right now,
she was so, so happy.

1385
01:29:40,917 --> 01:29:42,294
(WHISPERING)
What's going on here?

1386
01:29:44,588 --> 01:29:45,840
Relieved.

1387
01:29:46,298 --> 01:29:47,345
Oh, really?

1388
01:29:47,465 --> 01:29:49,843
Yes, I'm very sorry
to have wasted your time.

1389
01:29:55,307 --> 01:29:56,399
Well,

1390
01:29:56,850 --> 01:29:59,820
allow me to escort you, mademoiselle,
you know, as a precaution.

1391
01:30:00,562 --> 01:30:02,906
Would you?
I'm afraid I'm already late.

1392
01:30:03,023 --> 01:30:04,696
Right, Theo? Theo?

1393
01:30:05,191 --> 01:30:06,488
Coming, Meg?

1394
01:30:06,568 --> 01:30:07,660
Yes.

1395
01:30:09,446 --> 01:30:11,244
Right behind you.

1396
01:30:11,448 --> 01:30:12,950
(RECEPTIONIST
THANKING IN FRENCH)

1397
01:30:20,999 --> 01:30:22,091
How's it going in here?

1398
01:30:22,167 --> 01:30:23,760
Oh, we're good.

1399
01:30:23,835 --> 01:30:25,007
Just getting acquainted.

1400
01:30:26,046 --> 01:30:27,548
We Will...

1401
01:30:28,173 --> 01:30:30,801
We'll let you go as soon
as the auction is over.

1402
01:30:33,219 --> 01:30:34,846
Be right back.

1403
01:30:42,479 --> 01:30:43,776
MEG: Oh, come on.

1404
01:30:45,941 --> 01:30:47,193
Come on.

1405
01:30:48,693 --> 01:30:49,865
Promise

1406
01:30:52,572 --> 01:30:54,449
that whatever happens,

1407
01:30:56,117 --> 01:30:58,620
you'll think of the girl
you showed the fireworks to.

1408
01:31:02,290 --> 01:31:03,712
That was me.

1409
01:31:11,299 --> 01:31:14,269
Grace? Meg!

1410
01:31:14,719 --> 01:31:16,346
Owen! What are you doing here?

1411
01:31:17,097 --> 01:31:19,225
What's with...
Where's Emma?

1412
01:31:19,474 --> 01:31:20,726
She's upstairs.

1413
01:31:21,226 --> 01:31:22,728
Meg, is everything all right?

1414
01:31:22,811 --> 01:31:24,188
Yeah, everything's fine.

1415
01:31:24,354 --> 01:31:25,446
Where upstairs?

1416
01:31:25,522 --> 01:31:27,024
Trust me, you don't
want to go up there.

1417
01:31:27,649 --> 01:31:29,196
(IN ENGLISH ACCENT) Meg?
Yes?

1418
01:31:29,275 --> 01:31:30,276
Are you coming?
Coming.

1419
01:31:30,610 --> 01:31:31,953
Why is she talking
like that?

1420
01:31:32,028 --> 01:31:33,200
(G ROAN S) She's not.

1421
01:31:33,279 --> 01:31:35,122
Please, both of you,
just stay here.

1422
01:31:38,410 --> 01:31:39,411
Hey, mate.

1423
01:31:40,704 --> 01:31:42,422
Third floor.
Grimaldi Suite.

1424
01:31:43,873 --> 01:31:45,170
What did you tell him?

1425
01:31:45,250 --> 01:31:46,547
It's fine,
he's waiting with Riley.

1426
01:31:46,626 --> 01:31:48,594
BERNARD: (ANNOUNCING)
Miss Cordelia Winthrop Scott.

1427
01:31:54,759 --> 01:31:56,056
We've got this.

1428
01:32:00,724 --> 01:32:02,772
I’m really glad you came, Meg.

1429
01:32:04,936 --> 01:32:06,609
I wouldn't miss this
for the world.

1430
01:32:07,564 --> 01:32:08,907
(APPLAUSE)

1431
01:32:14,946 --> 01:32:16,914
You will never
get away with this.

1432
01:32:18,783 --> 01:32:21,502
Honey, we've been getting
away with this for days.

1433
01:32:23,204 --> 01:32:24,877
(DOORBELL CHIMING)

1434
01:32:26,374 --> 01:32:27,796
You... What?

1435
01:32:28,960 --> 01:32:30,553
Don't mess with Texas.

1436
01:32:30,628 --> 01:32:31,754
(EXCLAIMS)

1437
01:32:39,137 --> 01:32:40,138
Emma.

1438
01:32:40,263 --> 01:32:41,355
Owen?

1439
01:32:42,307 --> 01:32:43,729
What are you...
What are you doing here?

1440
01:32:43,808 --> 01:32:45,481
(STAMMERING)
What am I doing here?

1441
01:32:47,312 --> 01:32:49,189
What am I doing here?
I've been

1442
01:32:49,272 --> 01:32:50,865
running all over
Paris looking for you.

1443
01:32:52,859 --> 01:32:53,906
Hi.

1444
01:32:54,319 --> 01:32:55,320
Hi.

1445
01:32:56,613 --> 01:32:58,365
BERNARD: 1,000,000 eurOS.

1446
01:32:58,448 --> 01:32:59,791
'l,500,000.

1447
01:33:01,659 --> 01:33:03,707
We have a bid for 1.5.

1448
01:33:03,870 --> 01:33:05,213
'l,700,000.

1449
01:33:06,498 --> 01:33:07,624
Marvelous!

1450
01:33:08,333 --> 01:33:09,926
'l,700,000.

1451
01:33:12,462 --> 01:33:13,964
Do I hear two?

1452
01:33:19,552 --> 01:33:21,520
You went all the way
to Paris for me?

1453
01:33:24,390 --> 01:33:25,767
I don't want to
lose you, Emma.

1454
01:33:28,019 --> 01:33:29,942
Maybe I was trying
to fence you in a bit.

1455
01:33:30,897 --> 01:33:32,444
Guess I was just worried

1456
01:33:32,524 --> 01:33:34,526
that once you saw everything
there was to see here,

1457
01:33:34,609 --> 01:33:35,610
you wouldn't come back.

1458
01:33:35,693 --> 01:33:36,910
Owen...

1459
01:33:36,986 --> 01:33:39,080
And look,
I'm sorry for that,

1460
01:33:39,155 --> 01:33:41,203
because I don't ever want to
keep you from something better.

1461
01:33:42,659 --> 01:33:44,753
Emma,
you deserve the best.

1462
01:33:47,831 --> 01:33:49,959
But I already
have the best.

1463
01:33:54,420 --> 01:33:55,546
Yeah?

1464
01:33:56,131 --> 01:33:57,303
Yeah.

1465
01:34:00,885 --> 01:34:02,102
(THUDDING)

1466
01:34:02,720 --> 01:34:03,721
What was that?

1467
01:34:03,847 --> 01:34:04,848
(GRUNTING)

1468
01:34:04,931 --> 01:34:07,935
So, Paris. it's pretty
awesome, right?

1469
01:34:08,017 --> 01:34:09,143
What was that?

1470
01:34:09,227 --> 01:34:10,319
What was what, honey?
You heard it.

1471
01:34:10,395 --> 01:34:12,022
No, I didn't.
Is someone in there?

1472
01:34:12,939 --> 01:34:15,158
What? Is someone
in here? No.

1473
01:34:15,900 --> 01:34:17,322
Emma, what's going on?

1474
01:34:18,153 --> 01:34:19,245
Oh, shoot.

1475
01:34:19,320 --> 01:34:20,742
OWEN: Grace?

1476
01:34:21,156 --> 01:34:22,373
(LOUD APPLAUSE)

1477
01:34:22,448 --> 01:34:24,121
BERNARD:
We have a bid for 2.5.

1478
01:34:26,661 --> 01:34:28,629
Who Will bid 3,000,000 euros?

1479
01:34:31,124 --> 01:34:32,341
Anyone?

1480
01:34:33,084 --> 01:34:34,427
(IN NORMAL VOICE)
it's too much.

1481
01:34:34,794 --> 01:34:37,923
Mesdames et messieurs,
who will take us to 3,000,000?

1482
01:34:40,592 --> 01:34:41,844
Can I have...

1483
01:34:41,926 --> 01:34:43,098
Please, I'm sorry.

1484
01:34:43,636 --> 01:34:44,728
But,

1485
01:34:45,388 --> 01:34:46,765
my dear, what is wrong?

1486
01:34:52,395 --> 01:34:53,863
It's okay.

1487
01:34:55,857 --> 01:34:57,359
There's something
I need to say.

1488
01:34:57,442 --> 01:34:58,443
Of course.

1489
01:34:58,776 --> 01:35:00,119
What is it, Cordelia?

1490
01:35:02,947 --> 01:35:04,415
Gandhi once said...

1491
01:35:04,490 --> 01:35:05,707
Gandhi?

1492
01:35:05,992 --> 01:35:08,916
...that you must be
the change you wish

1493
01:35:10,455 --> 01:35:11,627
to see.

1494
01:35:12,123 --> 01:35:13,796
This necklace isn't mine.

1495
01:35:14,125 --> 01:35:15,627
(ALL MURMURING)

1496
01:35:16,044 --> 01:35:17,546
CORDELIA:
No, it's mine.

1497
01:35:20,590 --> 01:35:22,183
Arrest her,
she's an imposter.

1498
01:35:24,928 --> 01:35:25,975
Arrest her.

1499
01:35:26,054 --> 01:35:28,307
It's true.
I'm not Cordelia Scott.

1500
01:35:28,806 --> 01:35:30,103
There, you see?

1501
01:35:32,268 --> 01:35:34,487
I'm just a regular
girl from Texas.

1502
01:35:38,691 --> 01:35:40,443
I'm no one special,

1503
01:35:41,152 --> 01:35:43,280
but I had
the chance to be,

1504
01:35:44,239 --> 01:35:46,458
even if it was only for a
minute, and I took it.

1505
01:35:47,116 --> 01:35:48,413
We all did.

1506
01:35:48,493 --> 01:35:49,870
And we're sorry.

1507
01:35:50,995 --> 01:35:52,417
I know what
I did was wrong

1508
01:35:52,497 --> 01:35:54,920
and I don't expect
you to forgive me.

1509
01:35:58,002 --> 01:35:59,754
But it wasn't
all a lie.

1510
01:36:00,755 --> 01:36:02,507
I thought you were different.

1511
01:36:10,014 --> 01:36:12,062
$3,000,000.
(ALL GASP)

1512
01:36:12,183 --> 01:36:13,275
Owen.

1513
01:36:15,895 --> 01:36:17,613
We're from Texas,
we go big.

1514
01:36:17,689 --> 01:36:19,157
He doesn't have
any money.

1515
01:36:19,232 --> 01:36:20,984
Look at them,
none of them do.

1516
01:36:21,067 --> 01:36:22,740
Arrest them.
it's okay.

1517
01:36:22,860 --> 01:36:24,578
I'm sorry,
I didn't mean...

1518
01:36:24,654 --> 01:36:27,203
Look, you all came here
to help those kids.

1519
01:36:27,282 --> 01:36:30,411
Please don't let my mistake
get in the way of that.

1520
01:36:32,704 --> 01:36:34,502
I may not
deserve your help,

1521
01:36:36,207 --> 01:36:37,584
but they do.

1522
01:36:39,460 --> 01:36:41,212
ALICIA: 6,000,000 euros.

1523
01:36:41,296 --> 01:36:42,764
(ALL GASPING)

1524
01:36:43,631 --> 01:36:46,430
I would like to
bid 6,000,000 euros

1525
01:36:47,051 --> 01:36:48,143
for the necklace...

1526
01:36:48,219 --> 01:36:49,436
Aunt Alicia?

1527
01:36:49,512 --> 01:36:50,889
...on that young
woman's neck,

1528
01:36:52,223 --> 01:36:53,475
whomever she may be.

1529
01:36:55,268 --> 01:36:56,520
What are you doing?

1530
01:36:56,602 --> 01:36:59,321
I'm doing precisely
as she has asked.

1531
01:37:01,607 --> 01:37:03,075
I'm helping.

1532
01:37:04,068 --> 01:37:07,242
Sold for 6,000,000 euros
to one Miss Scott.

1533
01:37:08,197 --> 01:37:09,414
(CHUCKLING) Yeah!

1534
01:37:09,532 --> 01:37:11,079
No! But?

1535
01:37:25,423 --> 01:37:26,549
Thank you.

1536
01:37:28,551 --> 01:37:30,519
Why are you just standing there?
Arrest them!

1537
01:37:30,595 --> 01:37:32,393
For what?
They seem very nice.

1538
01:37:32,472 --> 01:37:33,689
They stole
my necklace.

1539
01:37:33,765 --> 01:37:35,233
But the necklace
is here, no?

1540
01:37:37,352 --> 01:37:39,275
Well, they kidnapped me
and they tied me up.

1541
01:37:39,354 --> 01:37:41,573
And yet,
you too are here.

1542
01:37:41,647 --> 01:37:43,945
I see no problem,
everybody is very happy.

1543
01:37:44,609 --> 01:37:47,237
Excuse me,
but I am not happy.

1544
01:37:47,320 --> 01:37:48,367
Hmm.

1545
01:37:48,446 --> 01:37:51,290
But this I can do
nothing about.

1546
01:37:57,246 --> 01:37:58,873
So, where to?

1547
01:38:00,083 --> 01:38:01,460
Let's go home.

1548
01:38:01,542 --> 01:38:04,421
GRACE: I don’t know, Meg. Have you really thought about this?

1549
01:38:04,504 --> 01:38:07,257
No! No, not at all.

1550
01:38:07,590 --> 01:38:08,933
But what did you
tell your dad?

1551
01:38:09,008 --> 01:38:11,010
Well, I told him I'd call
and check in every day,

1552
01:38:11,469 --> 01:38:13,267
that I won't tell him
everything I'm doing,

1553
01:38:13,346 --> 01:38:14,814
that I'll be back
in August,

1554
01:38:14,889 --> 01:38:16,141
and then

1555
01:38:16,682 --> 01:38:18,309
I hung up
very quickly.

1556
01:38:18,393 --> 01:38:19,394
(LAUGHS)

1557
01:38:24,857 --> 01:38:25,949
You,

1558
01:38:28,152 --> 01:38:29,825
take care of my sister.

1559
01:38:30,613 --> 01:38:32,331
RILEY:
Precious cargo.

1560
01:38:32,990 --> 01:38:35,084
My driver will take
you to the airport.

1561
01:38:37,703 --> 01:38:39,626
Bye,you
two lovebirds.

1562
01:38:44,168 --> 01:38:45,795
Please tell Theo
I said goodbye.

1563
01:38:47,088 --> 01:38:48,214
I will be sure to.

1564
01:38:49,715 --> 01:38:51,592
And that he was right.

1565
01:38:52,635 --> 01:38:53,636
I am different.

1566
01:38:54,220 --> 01:38:55,722
He knows that.

1567
01:38:57,306 --> 01:38:58,683
But I'll tell him.

1568
01:38:59,475 --> 01:39:00,818
Thank you.

1569
01:39:01,102 --> 01:39:02,194
Bye.

1570
01:39:14,532 --> 01:39:15,784
Au revoir!
See you later.

1571
01:39:15,867 --> 01:39:17,210
Au revoir.

1572
01:39:36,679 --> 01:39:38,272
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1573
01:39:42,894 --> 01:39:44,146
Hi, Mom

1574
01:39:45,646 --> 01:39:47,444
Yeah, we had
an amazing time.

1575
01:40:10,546 --> 01:40:11,718
(CHUCKLES)

1576
01:40:20,681 --> 01:40:22,558
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1577
01:40:26,687 --> 01:40:28,781
(RILEY WHOOPING)

1578
01:40:34,612 --> 01:40:36,159
(BOTH LAUGHING)

1579
01:40:55,132 --> 01:40:56,759
Just like that.

1580
01:40:56,968 --> 01:40:58,470
Try it out.

1581
01:41:43,723 --> 01:41:46,818
Hey, Grace, I need somebody
to run to the post office.

1582
01:41:47,351 --> 01:41:48,728
I'll do it.

1583
01:42:02,116 --> 01:42:03,538
That was it.

1584
01:42:03,618 --> 01:42:04,961
Yes, all right.

1585
01:42:05,036 --> 01:42:07,585
Now I am going to show you the
foundation of the new stadium,

1586
01:42:07,663 --> 01:42:11,338
which is possibly to be ready
by the end of the month.

1587
01:42:20,217 --> 01:42:22,436
We will have new lighting
for each classroom,

1588
01:42:22,511 --> 01:42:24,855
and the computers will
be here by September.

1589
01:42:25,806 --> 01:42:27,308
Superbe. Fine.

1590
01:42:30,186 --> 01:42:31,278
Thank you very much.

